params.message:
You will need 1 ethanol wells in the reservoir all with 10mL each, starting at A1.
                  Load 11.5ul of end prep mastermix in column 1 of D1 on temperature module.
You will need 1 bead column in the deepwell plate with 396.74999999999994, in A1.

End Prep MMX added. Place plate in thermal cycler, then back on the temperature module on C1.
                  Load 35.65ul of ligation mastermix in column 2 of D1 on temperature module.
Adapters added. Place in thermal cycler according to the end of section 1.3. Place plate back on temperature module on C1.
Beads cleanup completed. Continue with 1.5 Oxidation of 5-Methylcytosines and 5-Hydroxymethylcytosines. Samples are on the right half of the plate, starting in column 7.

First wash completed.
                  Load 19.549999999999997ul of tet2 mastermix in column 7 of D1 on temperature module.
                  Load 5.75ul of fe2 mastermix in column 8 of D1 on temperature module.
Take the plate to the thermal cycler according to section 1.5 of the SOP. Then, place back on the temperature module.

Completed step 1.6. Samples are in left half of plate on temperature module.
                 Safe stopping point. Samples at -20C overnight. Otherwise, select Resume for the robot to proceed to 1.7, adding formamide.
Load 5.75ul of formamide mastermix in column 9 of D1 on temperature module.

Formamide is added to samples WITHOUT pipette mixing. Move to thermal cycler.
                  Load 92.0ul of apobec mastermix in column 3 of deepwell reagent plate.
APOBEC added. Place in thermal cycler according to the end of section 1.8. Place plate back on temperature module on C1.
Samples are in right half of PCR plate. They can go overnight at -20C. Proceed on to 1.10 of SOP manually. Return plate to complete 1.11 of SOP.
Protocol completed! Samples are on left half of the plate on the temperature module, on slot D1.
